places.name: Maracas Bay

places.perex: La vecchia tenuta di zucchero è oggi il parco più popolare della città sia per l'esercizio fisico che per i vari eventi.

places.name: Nylon Pool
places.perex: Perhaps the best bathing spot on the islands. This is a real shallow pool far out in the sea, simply perfect for swimming.

places.name: Royal Botanic Gardens

places.name: Caroni Bird Sanctuary
places.perex: This vast swamp is one of the islands' most diverse ecosystems, best known for the many species of birds found here. Do not miss.

places.name: Paria Waterfall
places.perex: One of the more secluded waterfalls. The way here might be quite a hike, but the sight of the breath-taking waterfall is a great reward.

places.name: La Brea Pitch Lake

places.perex: The Red House is the seat of Parliament in the Republic of Trinidad and Tobago.

places.name: Saint Benedict's Roman Catholic Church
places.perex: Home to a peaceful monastery and one of the oldest monk communities in the Caribbean. Beautiful views and serene atmosphere.

places.name: Tobago Plantations Golf Course
places.perex: A relatively new par 72 course. Intriguing landscaping done on the site of a former coconut plantation.

places.name: YERETTé
places.perex: The private house is home to a huge number of hummingbirds you can meet up close. Call the owners and schedule a visit - you won't regret it.

places.name: Fort George
places.perex: A well-kept fort that used to belong to the British. Fun to explore and there's even a little museum.

places.name: Mayaro Beach
places.perex: Mayaro Bay stretches for nine miles on the east coast of the island of the Republic of Trinidad and Tobago.

places.name: Nariva Swamp
places.perex: The Nariva Swamp is the largest freshwater wetland in Trinidad and Tobago and has been designated a Wetland of International Importance…

places.name: Argyle Falls
places.perex: Several waterfalls connected by smaller pools. A marvellous sight and an enjoyable hike - notice the cocoa trees on the way there!

places.name: Piparo Mud Volcano
places.perex: Una delle curiosità naturali dell'isola. Il fango che bolle sia dentro sia intorno al vulcano è sicuramente una strana visione.

places.name: San Fernando Hill
places.perex: San Fernando Hill is a 192-m hill which lies at the centre of the city of San Fernando in Trinidad and Tobago.

places.name: Devil's Woodyard
places.perex: Devil's Woodyard is one of the most visited locations of Trinidad's many mud volcanoes.

places.name: Tracking Station

places.name: Nelson Island
places.perex: Nelson Island, Trinidad and Tobago is one of the Five Islands which lie west of Port of Spain in the Gulf of Paria.

places.name: Waterloo Temple in the Sea
places.perex: An awe-inspiring Hindu temple built right in the sea. Truly a fascinating sight - go inside if you can.

places.name: Brian Lara Promenade
places.name_suffix: Port of Spain, Trinidad and Tobago
places.perex: The heart of the busy city. Great for picture-taking, people-watching or tasting the street food from one of the local vendors.

places.name: National Museum & Art Gallery
places.name_suffix: Port of Spain, Trinidad and Tobago
places.perex: The National Museum and Art Gallery is the national museum of Trinidad and Tobago, in Port of Spain on Trinidad island.

places.name: Store Bay
places.perex: A lovely little beach with many facilities to get you through the day. Even the locals come by here often.

places.name: Buccoo Beach
places.perex: A long, sandy beach. The sea is not very clean here, but you can still walk around and see the various lizards that hang out here.

places.name: Manzanilla Beach
places.perex: Even though waters may be rough at times here, this beach is still wonderful and possibly one of the best on the islands.

places.name: Englishman's Bay
places.perex: A peaceful beach that is deserted most of the time. A picturesque spot great for snorkelling and other activities.

places.name: Arnos Vale Waterwheel and Nature Park
places.perex: Once a great plantation and sugar factory, now it lies it ruins. If you're into adventure and exploring, this is your place.

places.name: Anna Reef
places.perex: This long reef extends farther than you'd expect. You can see all sorts of corals and other marine life on this diving site.

places.name: Fort Abercromby
places.perex: Built by the British to protect the bay nearby. Has barely been used, but nowadays, it's an atmospheric ruin.

places.name: Angel Reef
places.perex: This shallow reef is a favourite destination amongst both snorkellers and divers. A fun and rewarding spot with lots of marine life.

places.name: Courland Monument
places.perex: Devoted to the settlers of this area and the oldest settlement on the island of Tobago. Interesting monument and great views.

places.name: Main Ridge Forest Reserve
places.perex: This vast area is covered with tropical rainforest. Plenty of opportunities for bird-watching, hiking and getting to know the local nature.

places.name: Maracas Waterfall
places.perex: Easily accessible, scenic waterfall. A beautiful sight that is unfortunately spoiled by the garbage left here by the locals.

places.name: El Cerro del Aripo
places.perex: El Cerro del Aripo è il punto più elevato di Trinidad e Tobago, con un'altitudine di 940 metri s.l.m..

places.perex: Hollis Reservoir is a reservoir located in north Trinidad and it supplies Arima, Port of Spain and other areas of north Trinidad.

places.name: Republic Bank
places.perex: Republic Bank is a bank and financial service provider in Trinidad and Tobago and one of the largest in the Eastern Caribbean.

places.name: Pointe-à-Pierre Wild Fowl Trust

places.name: Buccoo Reef
places.perex: Said to be the best reef on the islands for its accessible marine life. Snorkelling, diving and glass boat tours are all popular here.

places.name: Millennium Lakes
places.perex: An 18-hole course with plenty of water hazards to keep you on your toes. Facilities include putting greens and a lit driving range.

places.name: Mount Irvine Bay Golf Course
places.perex: 18-hole, par 72 course with plenty of facilities and a long tradition. Perhaps the best course on all of the islands.

places.name: St. Andrews Golf Club
places.perex: An 18-hole course and one of the oldest on the islands. Provides a truly challenging play with its undulating terrain and bunkers.

places.name: The Cathedral of the Immaculate Conception
places.name_suffix: Port of Spain, Trinidad and Tobago
places.perex: The imposing cathedral with its two towers is perhaps an unexpected sight on the islands, but well worth the visit.

places.name: Maha Sabha Indian Museum
places.perex: The Indian Caribbean Museum of Trinidad and Tobago in Waterloo, on Trinidad, Trinidad and Tobago.

places.name: Quinam Beach
places.perex: This well-facilitated beach with its slow, rocking waves is a popular spot not just for swimming, but also fishing and camping.

places.name: Aripo Cave

places.name: El Tucuche
places.perex: El Tucuche is the second highest peak in Trinidad's northern range and is noted for its interesting plateau shape.

places.name: Petrotrin Pointe-à-Pierre Golf Club
places.perex: An 18-hole course with water hazards to keep you on your toes. Especially the last few holes can prove to be quite a challenge.

places.name: Brechin Castle Golf Course
places.perex: An 18-hole golf course still sporting a classical layout from the beginning of the 20th century. A pleasant and relaxing place where to play.

places.name: Chaguaramas Golf Course
places.perex: A secluded 9-hole golf course developed on the site of a former plantation. The trees provide wonderful scenery.

places.name: Trinity Cathedral
places.name_suffix: Port of Spain, Trinidad and Tobago
places.perex: An Anglican cathedral and one of the islands' oldest landmarks. Recently reconstructed and simply beautiful.

places.name: Being with Horses
places.perex: Horseback-riding at its finest. Run by very friendly owners and offering beachside rides on well-cared for, happy horses.

places.name: Tamana Caves
places.perex: Tamana caves is a cave system located on the northern slope of Mount Tamana in eastern Trinidad.

places.name: BUZO Osteria Italiana
places.name_suffix: Port of Spain, Trinidad and Tobago
places.perex: A modern and chic restaurant serving Italian-influenced dishes. Well worth the visit, special occasion or not.

places.name: University of the West Indies, Tobago
La Vega Garden Centre
places.perex: The estate's main pride are its gardens - perfect for picnicking, fishing, and generally forgetting about all your worries.

places.name: Las Cuevas Bay
places.perex: A popular sheltered beach with great swimming conditions, but there are also some caves for you to explore if you get bored.

places.name: Charlotteville
places.perex: One of the most charming villages on the islands and a true getaway. This fishing community has its own unique atmosphere.

places.name: Adventure Farm and Nature Reserve
places.perex: A small, but terrific estate well-worth the visit. Mainly serves as a bird station - especially the hummingbirds are charming.

places.name: Spa Esencia
places.name_suffix: Port of Spain, Trinidad and Tobago
places.perex: A luxurious spa offering massages, manicures, pedicures and much more. The place to go if you want to pamper yourself.

places.name: The Waterfront Restaurant
places.name_suffix: Port of Spain, Trinidad and Tobago
places.perex: An upscale restaurant serving seafood and more. Fancy atmosphere and pleasant service  are its main perks.

places.name: Kimme Museum
places.perex: The artist herself has made her own home her gallery. Come see her intriguing sculptures depicting the locals.

places.name: The Seahorse Inn
places.perex: Both international and Caribbean cuisine is served at this outstanding restaurant. Great atmosphere and lovely location.

places.name: La Cantina
places.perex: Authentic Italian pizzas are not impossible to find on Tobago. But beware - the restaurant often gets crowded (and for a reason).

places.name: London Bridge
places.perex: This diving site is well-known for its unusual terrain, but also colourful marine life. A challenging, but spectacular dive.

places.name: Arnos Vale Reef
places.perex: A peaceful beach with a terrific reef right next to it. Suits both snorkellers and divers and makes for a very relaxing diving spot.

places.name: The Trunk Show
places.name_suffix: Port of Spain, Trinidad and Tobago

places.name: Khalian Systems
places.name_suffix: Port of Spain, Trinidad and Tobago

places.name: Grange Beach
places.perex: Quite and tranquil beach with soft golden sands - just like the one they show in the commercials.

places.name: Fish City
places.perex: The name speaks for itself - you can spot all kinds of fish, the occasional shark and a lot of nice corals here.

places.name: Fort Bennett
places.perex: This British fort is said to have experienced many fights. Today, it's a tranquil place with lush greenery and only a few cannons.

places.name: Tyrico Beach
places.perex: This small beach with brown sands has its own charm - a terrific place for some sun and sea bathing in private.

places.name: Pirate's Bay
places.perex: Best known for its pristine beach and rougher waters that still allow for snorkelling. A true secluded gem.

places.name: Castara Bay Beach
places.perex: A picture-perfect, unspoilt beach. Great for swimming, snorkelling, tanning and all the other beach activities.

places.name: Gasparee Caves
places.perex: These caves hide a system of tunnels that were supposedly used by the pirates to hide their treasure. They look quite marvellous, too.

places.name: Canoe Bay Beach
places.perex: A secluded and calm beach that makes for a great snorkelling spot. At low tide, you can walk far out into the sea.

places.name: Mount Irvine Bay Beach
places.perex: Actually two beaches that are connected at low tide. A popular spot that can get a little crowded, but is worth the visit.

places.name: Toco Beach
places.perex: A picture-perfect beach that is almost always deserted. Great for surfing, enjoying the shade of the palm trees and watching turtles nesting.

places.name: MV Maverick
places.perex: A former car ferry that was deliberately sunk about 15 years ago. Nowadays it's turned into a beautiful artificial reef.

places.name: Stonehaven Bay
places.perex: A great beach with some strong waves and currents. The leatherback turtles come to nest here in the season.

places.name: Runway
places.perex: This drift reef dive is not very deep or complicated, but the marine life is certainly present here.

places.name: Genesis Nature Park & Art Gallery
places.perex: Serves as an art gallery where the owner displays his works and also as a small petting zoo with some unusual animals.

places.name: Los Iros Beach
places.perex: The beach is still popular with windsurfers, although the times when it was a holiday resort are long gone (and so are the crowds).

places.name: Diver's Dream
places.perex: Away from the island, this diving spot is rich on all sorts of marine life you won't see closer to shore.

places.name: Fort James
places.perex: One of the oldest forts on the islands built by the Latvian settlers. A good way of exploring the island's history.

places.name: Hanuman Murti
places.perex: Hindu is a prominent religion on the islands and so it's not surprising that there is a huge and colourful statue of a Hindu god here.

places.name: Kariwak
places.perex: This reef makes for a terrific beginner dive - it's close to the beach and there are no drifts. The marine life is very rich here.

places.name: Black Jack Hole
places.perex: The current are strong which makes this a challenging drift dive, but the turtles and other marine life you will see is a nice reward.

places.name: Jemma's Sea View Kitchen Tree House
places.perex: A gorgeous restaurant serving delicious Caribbean meal. The setting is great, too - right by the sea.

places.name: Kelleston Drain
places.perex: This dive site holds the largest brain coral in the world. An enormous sight often visited by manta rays and sharks.

places.name: Dillons
places.perex: A fabulous restaurant that combines flavours from all around the world with seafood. An outstanding establishment.

places.name: Little Tobago
places.perex: The little island is well-known for its untouched nature and amazing birdwatching opportunities. The views from here are grand, too.

places.name: Chagville Beach
places.perex: A man-made, well-facilitated beach with golden sands and wind-surfing opportunities. Other sports are also popular here.

places.name: Japanese Gardens
places.perex: As the name suggests, this is one of the prettiest underwater spots around the islands. The fish and sharks like to hang out here, too.

places.name: Stingray Alley
places.perex: As the name suggests, this deeper dive's main attraction are stingrays, but you can also meet guitarfish here.

places.name: Bookends
places.perex: A challenging dive with strong currents in some parts, but totally worth it - many kinds of marine life roam around here.

places.name: Flagstaff Hill
places.perex: If you're looking for stunning sunset views, this hill can provide them. A great place for an evening picnic.

places.name: Tobago Museum
places.perex: A small but intriguing museum depicting Tobago's history, both Pre-Columbian and colonial. Many artefacts here.

places.name: Apsara Restaurant
places.name_suffix: Port of Spain, Trinidad and Tobago
places.perex: The islands' Indian heritage comes alive here. If you're longing for some curry or other delicious dishes, do not hesitate to visit.

places.name: Chaguaramas Military History Museum
places.perex: Explore the two world wars from the islands' perspective. A captivating museum with plenty of authentic artefacts on display.

places.name: Flying Reef
places.perex: A diving site with strong currents, but also barracudas, turtles and other marine life. Quite huge.

places.name: Knolly’s Tunnel
places.perex: The longest train tunnel in the Caribbean has been slowly abandoned over the years, but it hasn't lost its genius loci.

places.name: Matura Beach
places.perex: This vast, unspoilt beach is not known as a bathing spot, but as a nesting place of leatherback turtles. A magical sight.

places.name: Grafton Caledonia Wildlife Sanctuary
places.perex: A former cocoa plantation that has been transformed into a sanctuary. Home to friendly birds which you can feed from your hand.

places.name: Fort Milford
places.perex: A small and peaceful British fort that has its own special atmosphere. Small, but worth the visit - and the sunsets are amazing here.
